    "body": "**Description of the problem**\r\nI would like to use pygmt to set a bunch of global configuration variables. This would be done at the beginning of a script and would apply to all new figures.\r\n\r\nThe problem is that when you create a new figure, the previously set configuration variables appear to be reset to their default values, as shown here:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport pygmt\r\n\r\npygmt.config(MAP_FRAME_PEN=\"blue\",\r\n             MAP_TICK_PEN=\"blue\",\r\n             FONT_ANNOT_PRIMARY=\"blue\",\r\n             FONT_LABEL=\"blue\")\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\nfig.basemap(region=[0, 10, 0, 10],\r\n            projection=\"X15c/15c\",\r\n            frame=[\"SNWE\", \"yaf+ly\", \"xaf+lx\"])\r\nfig.show(method='external')\r\n```\r\n![test](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8697285/130817493-75403c88-eb07-4b04-9a28-076f5650f6bf.png)\r\n\r\nHowever, if I create the figure first, and then set the config variables, everything works as expected\r\n```\r\nimport pygmt\r\n\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\npygmt.config(MAP_FRAME_PEN=\"blue\",\r\n             MAP_TICK_PEN=\"blue\",\r\n             FONT_ANNOT_PRIMARY=\"blue\",\r\n             FONT_LABEL=\"blue\")\r\nfig.basemap(region=[0, 10, 0, 10],\r\n            projection=\"X15c/15c\",\r\n            frame=[\"SNWE\", \"yaf+ly\", \"xaf+lx\"])\r\nfig.show(method='external')\r\n```\r\n![test2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8697285/130817855-45229bc9-230b-447f-92f1-ea70c8d272f7.png)\r\n\r\nIf this behavior is in fact by design, the question is: How can I change the default configuration values ?\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\nPlease paste the output of `python -c \"import pygmt; pygmt.show_versions()\"`:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPyGMT information:\r\n  version: v0.3.1\r\nSystem information:\r\n  python: 3.9.6 | packaged by conda-forge | (default, Jul 11 2021, 03:36:15)  [Clang 11.1.0 ]\r\n  executable: /opt/miniconda3/envs/py39b/bin/python\r\n  machine: macOS-11.5.2-x86_64-i386-64bit\r\nDependency information:\r\n  numpy: 1.21.2\r\n  pandas: 1.3.2\r\n  xarray: 0.18.2\r\n  netCDF4: 1.5.6\r\n  packaging: 21.0\r\n  ghostscript: 9.54.0\r\n  gmt: 6.1.1\r\nGMT library information:\r\n  binary dir: /opt/miniconda3/envs/py39b/bin\r\n  cores: 8\r\n  grid layout: rows\r\n  library path: /opt/miniconda3/envs/py39b/lib/libgmt.dylib\r\n  padding: 2\r\n  plugin dir: /opt/miniconda3/envs/py39b/lib/gmt/plugins\r\n  share dir: /opt/miniconda3/envs/py39b/share/gmt\r\n  version: 6.1.1\r\n```\r\n",
